wikipedia_page.main: Rupert Ashby Cave Rogers (27 May 1902 – 2 May 1976) was an English cricketer who played a single first-class match, a friendly for Worcestershire against Warwickshire in 1919. Batting at three in his only innings, he made only 3. He took no wickets from his five overs, but held one catch, to dismiss Warwickshire opener Horace Venn.Rogers was later known as Rupert Ashby Cave-Rogers.

response: * Rupert Rogers (1902 in Tixall – 1976) an English cricketer who played a single first-class match for Worcestershire
